1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,115
Night owls watching at 2 AM — I see you.

2
00:00:04,065 --> 00:00:07,486
Let's make this study session count.

3
00:00:07,486 --> 00:00:17,881
Without EOS, you face a dilemma: - At-most-once: commit offset before processing → crash between commit and processing → message skipped.

4
00:00:17,881 --> 00:00:27,000
At-least-once: commit offset after processing → crash between processing and commit → message reprocessed → duplicate effect.

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:36,052
Plot twist: ChatGPT uses the exact same concepts we're learning here to handle millions of concurrent users.

